headline: Intercontinental Exchange Revenue, Profit Increase
summary: Intercontinental Exchange  reported higher top- and bottom-line results in its latest quarter.  The company, which operates a network of exchanges and clearing houses, reported net income of $851 million, or $1.48 a share, for the second quarter, up from $632 million, or $1.10 a share, in the prior-year period.  Analysts polled by FactSet expected $1.77 a share.
